    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='29113#1459357643'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-03-30T17:07:23+00:00">Mar 30, 2016 05:07 PM UTC</time> by <b>Dave Dykstra</b><a class="anchor" name="1459357643">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Thanks for the details, Jim.

I just talked to Mine, she&#39;s OK with going forward with this, so I plan to do so.  It&#39;s just something she didn&#39;t think much about when she made the initial specification.  She is also quite interested in having it supported on CILogon Basic CA so those who get those certs only need to get one.

I plan to specify what the Digicert-Grid End entity user certs have, which is&#58;
X509v3 Extended Key Usage&#58;
TLS Web Client Authentication, E-mail Protection
I do not plan to change the End entity host/service certificate flags because those already match what was in Digicert-Grid certs.

Thanks for the links to free email certificates.  I wasn&#39;t aware of them, but I checked and Comodo at least says they&#39;re for personal/home use only, so I don&#39;t think OSG people would be able to use them for work.  I didn&#39;t find a restriction like that on StartSSL but it does talk about the level of assurance being pretty low because people can get certificates by only verifying email.  Yes it is a little trouble for people to add the CA cert to their email clients, but once they do they can have assurance that the identities of individuals they work with were better verified.

I&#39;m going to go ahead and close this ticket.  There will be a separate ticket for requesting the change when it has been approved.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='29113#1459346857'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-03-30T14:07:37+00:00">Mar 30, 2016 02:07 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1459346857">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>1. Sorry, I have no experience with the &#34;id-kp-emailProtection&#34; flag upon which to base a recommendation, so I recommend matching the configuration that OSG has used successfully in the past with other CAs -- something I thought we had already done.
2. Send email to the tagpma-general mailing list (<a href='https&#58;//groups.google.com/a/tagpma.org/group/tagpma-general' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//groups.google.com/a/tagpma.org/group/tagpma-general</a>). See Section 9.12.1 of the CP/CPS for the full procedure. Here&#39;s an example email notification&#58; <a href='https&#58;//groups.google.com/a/tagpma.org/forum/#' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//groups.google.com/a/tagpma.org/forum/#</a>!topic/tagpma-general/59aK27Hz-_8
3. There is a customary 2 week TAGPMA comment period before implementing CP/CPS changes.
4. If the testing goes well with OSG, we&#39;ll probably also add the flag to other CILogon certificates, though in my opinion the usefulness is limited by the fact that the CILogon CAs are not trusted by email clients, so using them for email signing requires recipients to manually add the CILogon CAs to their email client configuration. There are multiple providers of free, trusted email signing certificates that I&#39;d recommend instead (e.g., <a href='https&#58;//startssl.com/' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//startssl.com/</a> and <a href='https&#58;//www.comodo.com/home/email-security/free-email-certificate.php' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//www.comodo.com/home/email-security/free-email-certificate.php</a>).

by /DC=org/DC=cilogon/C=US/O=University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign/CN=James Basney A534</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='29113#1459301274'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-03-30T01:27:54+00:00">Mar 30, 2016 01:27 AM UTC</time> by <b>Dave Dykstra</b><a class="anchor" name="1459301274">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Jim,

That sounds simple enough.  I&#39;ll plan on trying to get hold of Mine to make sure she&#39;s OK with it and if so, do that.

Some questions about the details&#58;
1. I know it makes sense to have this on the End entity personal certificates, but do you have a recommendation on whether or not to enable this on End entity host/service certificates?&#34;
2. How exactly do I notify the TAGPMA?
3. Does the TAGPMA only need to be notified, or do we need to wait until they approve?

Also a related question&#58; are there plans to enable this feature for CILogon Basic CA certificates?  That seems very useful as well.

Dave</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='29113#1459289803'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-03-29T22:16:43+00:00">Mar 29, 2016 10:16 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1459289803">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>CILogon can change the contents of the X509v3 Extended Key Usage certificate extension according to OSG&#39;s specifications. I think OSG will need to update Section 7.1.2 of the CILogon OSG CA CP/CPS (<a href='https&#58;//twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/OSGCertificateService' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/OSGCertificateService</a>), notify TAGPMA of the change, and then initiate the change management process (<a href='https&#58;//twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/ChangeMgmtWithCILogonHSM' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/ChangeMgmtWithCILogonHSM</a>) whereby CILogon first makes the change in our test instance and then with OSG&#39;s approval CILogon makes the change in production.

by /DC=org/DC=cilogon/C=US/O=University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign/CN=James Basney A534</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='29113#1459286226'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-03-29T21:17:06+00:00">Mar 29, 2016 09:17 PM UTC</time> by <b>Dave Dykstra</b><a class="anchor" name="1459286226">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Currently, user certificates created by the OSG CA can&#39;t be used to sign email.  I&#39;ve heard that Terry said &#34;The certificates created by the CILogon service are not suitable for email signing/encryption since they lack the &#34;id-kp-emailProtection&#34; flag in the &#34;Extended Key Usage&#34; x509v3 extension.&#34;

My question is, can that be changed, and if so, what would it take?</pre></div><legend>Similar Recent Tickets <small>modified within the last 30 days</small></legend><div id="similar_tickets"><p class="muted">No similar tickets found.</p></div>
